<h2>Be ready</h2>

Please use the resources below to prepare yourself and your loved ones in the event of a disaster incident.
A disaster in our area can include an earthquake, volcanic eruption, terrorist attack, or other devastating incidents.
The <a href="http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2015/07/20/the-really-big-one" target="_blank">New Yorker</a>
recently published an article addressing the aftermath of an earthquake that will affect our area. Aside from
the lack of electricity and clean water for weeks or months, there will be panic and serious injuries.<p>

The City of Kirkland has an emergency response team that offers CERT training to individuals that are willing to assist
others in the case of an incident. The 8 week course is offered 2 times a year and costs $40. There are free online
courses through FEMA as well.<p>

